&gt;What is the correct way that retailers should refund an item purchased with
&gt;a coupon?

"/> The correct way is to undo the transaction: you give them back the
item you got, and they give you back the money and coupon they got.

If they can't return the coupon, then you're correct that they
should return its value to you -- the consumer amount, not including
the handling fee that the manufacturer pays them.

Unfortunately, this is one of those situations where enforcing your
legal rights would cost many times the value of those rights. Much
better to try to get a manager to agree with you.

