"/> What's your reason for return?

If the reason is that the item was defective or otherwise unfit for
merchantability, they should exchange it for a working item, or else
reasonable damages (e.g. a voucher or replacement cost reimbursement for an
equivalent item that does work.)

If the reason is that you just don't want it anymore, they owe you nothing
more than what the return policy says. If you don't like their offer for
buying a used product back from you, sell it to someone else.

Disclaimer: I am not a lawyer and none of this is legal advice (You asked
what was &quot;right&quot;, not what was legal.)

